## Troubleshooting Upload Issues

### "File Too Large" Error

**Solutions:**
1. ‚úÖ Compress file:
   - Right-click ‚Üí Send to ‚Üí Compressed folder (ZIP)
   - Use 7-Zip for better compression
2. ‚úÖ Resize images:
   - Use TinyPNG.com
   - Reduce resolution
   - Compress JPG quality
3. ‚úÖ Split large files:
   - Use file splitter
   - Upload in parts
4. ‚úÖ Use cloud storage:
   - Upload to Google Drive/Dropbox
   - Share link in comments

### "File Type Not Supported" Error

**Solutions:**
1. ‚úÖ Check extension is allowed
2. ‚úÖ ZIP the file first
3. ‚úÖ Convert to PDF (for documents)
4. ‚úÖ Contact admin to allow type

### Upload Stuck/Frozen

**Solutions:**
1. ‚úÖ Check internet connection
   - Try other websites
   - Run speed test
2. ‚úÖ Try smaller files first
3. ‚úÖ Clear browser cache:
   - Ctrl+Shift+Del
   - Clear all
   - Restart browser
4. ‚úÖ Try different browser
5. ‚úÖ Disable VPN temporarily
6. ‚úÖ Disable browser extensions

### "Upload Failed" Error

**Solutions:**
1. ‚úÖ Check file isn't corrupted:
   - Try opening file
   - Try from different location
2. ‚úÖ Upload one at a time
3. ‚úÖ Check disk space on your device
4. ‚úÖ Try different file format
5. ‚úÖ Contact support if persists

## File Storage & Security

### Where Files Stored

**Server Storage:**
- Secure cloud servers
- Encrypted at rest
- Daily backups
- Redundant storage
- Geographic replication

### Access Control

**Who Can View:**
- ‚úÖ Ticket requester (you)
- ‚úÖ Assigned engineer
- ‚úÖ Engineers with `can_view_all_tickets`
- ‚úÖ Department manager
- ‚úÖ System administrators

**Who Cannot:**
- ‚ùå Other regular users
- ‚ùå Users in different departments (unless admin)
- ‚ùå Public/anonymous access

### Retention Policy

**How Long Kept:**
- Files kept for life of ticket
- Deleted when ticket deleted (by admin)
- Backup copies for 30 days
- Audit trail maintained

**Deletion:**
- Admin can delete attachments
- Users can request deletion (privacy)
- Automatic after ticket purge (if configured)

### Security Scanning

**All uploads:**
- ‚úÖ Scanned for viruses
- ‚úÖ Malware detection
- ‚úÖ Suspicious files quarantined
- ‚úÖ Security team notified of threats
- ‚úÖ Encrypted in transit (HTTPS)

**Safe to download:** If uploaded by trusted source

## Best Practices

### ‚úÖ DO

**General:**
- Attach files when creating ticket
- Use clear, descriptive filenames
- Compress multiple files as ZIP
- Screenshot entire error messages
- Include log files for technical issues
- Redact sensitive information
- Use PNG for screenshots

**For Better Results:**
- Annotate screenshots (arrows, circles)
- Provide multiple angles/views
- Include before/after screenshots
- Add file in comments if forgot initially

### ‚ùå DON'T

**Avoid:**
- Attaching executable files directly
- Using phone photos of screen
- Uploading huge uncompressed files
- Including passwords in screenshots
- Forgetting to attach promised files
- Attaching irrelevant files
- Using unclear filenames ("image1.png")

## File Limits Summary

| Limit Type | Value |
|------------|-------|
| Max File Size | 10 MB |
| Max Files Per Ticket | 5 files |
| Max Total Size | 50 MB |
| Allowed Formats | PDF, DOC, XLS, Images, ZIP, TXT |
| Blocked Formats | EXE, BAT, Scripts |

## Common Questions

**Q: Can I attach files after ticket created?**
A: Yes! Open ticket ‚Üí Attachments tab ‚Üí Upload.

**Q: Can I delete attachments?**
A: Only admins can delete. Comment which file to ignore if you attached wrong one.

**Q: Are my files private?**
A: Files visible only to ticket participants and authorized support staff.

**Q: Can I attach files in comments?**
A: Not directly in comment text, but use Attachments tab and reference in comment.

**Q: What if I need to attach more than 5 files?**
A: ZIP multiple files together, or use cloud storage and share link.

**Q: Can I download attachments from closed tickets?**
A: Yes, attachments remain downloadable even after ticket closed.

## Related Articles

- Creating Effective Tickets
- Taking Good Screenshots
- Troubleshooting Upload Issues
- Security & Privacy

---

**Remember:** Good attachments = Faster resolution! üìé‚ú®`,
